                <h2 class="subheading">Top 5 Royal Enfield Bikes in India (2025 Edition)</h2>
                @* <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.BlogSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p> *@
                <p>
                    Royal Enfield has long been a name etched in the hearts of Indian motorcyclists. With a legacy that stretches over a century, the brand has managed to evolve while maintaining its iconic character. Whether it’s the unmistakable thump of the engine, the retro-inspired design, or the rugged simplicity, Royal Enfield bikes continue to be the top choice for riders across age groups and terrains.</p>
                <p>
                    As we move into 2025, Royal Enfield’s portfolio offers something for everyone—from seasoned highway tourers to city commuters and off-road adventurers. Here’s a look at the <span class="font-weight-700"> top 5 Royal Enfield bikes in India for 2025 </span> that stand out for their performance, styling, features, and value
                </p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Criteria for Selection</h3>
                <p>The bikes listed here are chosen based on several key factors:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine performance and efficiency</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Ride quality and comfort</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Design and road presence</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Technological upgrades</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Market popularity and overall value</span></li>
                </ul>
                <p>These models represent a diverse mix, targeting different kinds of riders—urban commuters, cruisers, off-roaders, and those who simply love the charm of a classic.</p>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="RoyalEnfield" asp-action="REClassic350">1. Royal Enfield Classic 350 – The Timeless Icon</a></h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/may/top5royalenfieldbikesinindia/reclassic350.png" alt="bikecarhubreclassic350" title="bikecarhubreclassic350" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>No Royal Enfield list is complete without the <span class="font-weight-700"> Classic 350 </span>, the brand’s signature motorcycle that merges heritage with modern refinement. Updated to meet current norms, the 2025 Classic 350 features a <span class="font-weight-700"> 349.34cc air-cooled engine </span> delivering <span class="font-weight-700"> 20.21 PS </span> and <span class="font-weight-700"> 27 Nm </span> of torque.</p>
                <p>What makes the Classic 350 a perennial favorite is its effortless charm—a round headlamp, vintage-style fuel tank, and chrome touches all blend into a retro design. It also gets <span class="font-weight-700"> dual-channel ABS, semi-digital instrument cluster <span class="font-weight-700">, and improved suspension for better comfort.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Ex-showroom Price (2025): ₹1.93 – ₹2.25 lakh</span></p>
                <p>
                    <span class="font-weight-700">Key Highlights:</span>
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Old-school charm with new-age performance</li>
                    <li>Comfortable and refined ride</li>
                    <li>Strong resale value</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Specification & Features</span></p>
				<ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine Type:</span> 349.34 cc, air-cooled engine</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Mileage:</span> 41.5 kmpl</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Power:</span> 20.21 PS@6100 rpm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Fuel Capacity:</span> 13 L</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Max Torque:</span> 27 Nm@4000 rpm</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="RoyalEnfield" asp-action="REInterceptor650">2. Royal Enfield Interceptor 650 – The Retro Roadster</a></h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/may/top5royalenfieldbikesinindia/RE Interceptor 650.png" alt="bikecarhub Royal Enfield Interceptor 650" title="bikecarhub Royal Enfield Interceptor 650" /></div>
                </div>
                <p> The <span class="font-weight-700"> Interceptor 650 </span> remains one of the best-value twin-cylinder motorcycles in India. Launched as part of Royal Enfield's modern classic revolution, it features a <span class="font-weight-700"> 648cc parallel-twin engine </span> producing about <span class="font-weight-700"> 47.4 PS </span> and <span class="font-weight-700"> 52.3 Nm </span> of torque, offering strong highway performance and exceptional ride quality. </p>
                <p> The 2025 edition is expected to see minor tweaks, possibly including alloy wheels and updated electronics. Its retro styling, upright riding position, and refined power delivery make it suitable for both city commutes and highway sprints. </p>
                <p> <span class="font-weight-700"> Ex-showroom Price (2025): ₹3.03 – ₹3.31 lakh </span> </p>
                <p> <span class="font-weight-700"> Key Highlights: </span> </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Smooth and powerful twin-cylinder engine</li>
                    <li>Retro looks with modern reliability</li>
                    <li>Great for both new and experienced riders</li>
				</ul>
