                </div>
                <p>The <span class="font-weight-700"> Royal Enfield Himalayan 450 </span> is the brand’s most advanced offering in the adventure segment, designed to conquer everything from Ladakh’s high passes to coastal trails. It features a <span class="font-weight-700">452cc liquid-cooled engine </span> that produces an impressive <span class="font-weight-700">40.02 PS of power </span> and <span class="font-weight-700">40 Nm of torque </span>—a huge leap over its predecessor.</p>
                <p>With <span class="font-weight-700">long-travel suspension, a robust new chassis, switchable ABS, </span> and <span class="font-weight-700">spoke wheels </span> with dual-purpose tyres, the Himalayan 450 is made for those who prefer to ride beyond the limits of tarmac. It also gets modern touches like a fully digital TFT display with smartphone connectivity and turn-by-turn navigation.</p>
